    "summary": "Completed MSc in Plant Sciences, Crop Science at Wageningen University. Conducted field research for MSc thesis in Tamil Nadu, India on adoption of the System of Rice Intensification and field work for MSc internship in Ethiopia for development of a Code of Practice for the Ethiopian horticulture sector. After graduation worked on a short assignment in Costa Rica developing a market research report on the horticulture sector of Central America; worked for several years as horticultural consultant for the Dutch horticulture sector; worked at DLV Plant (currently Delphy) as project manager & advisor international projects with focus on the horticulture sector of East Africa; volunteer at the 1%Club as project coach; agricultural expert for Agriterra\u2019s Agripool for short missions or assignments in developing countries; conducted a short assignment at Solidaridad; associate consultant at Wageningen Centre for Development Innovation, Wageningen University & Research.\n\nCurrently I am working at the Wageningen Centre for Development Innovation, Wageningen University & Research, as Advisor & Project Manager Horticulture Sector Transformation.\n\nI have a passion for international agricultural development. My curious nature, broad expertise, and flexible attitude makes me an interdisciplinary person with the capacity to work in complex and challenging contexts and in multidisciplinary projects and teams. I am able to combine both theoretical and practical knowledge in the food systems domain, designing and implementing both conceptual and applied approaches.\n\nI have experience in the field of consultancy, project management, training design & facilitation and research.\n\nMy professional life has taken me so far to India, Ethiopia, Costa Rica, Kenya, Indonesia, Ghana, Jordan, Nepal and Rwanda.\n\nSpecialties: agricultural systems, food systems, sector development & transformation, agricultural research, plant & crop production, integrated pest management, agribusiness, agricultural value chains, sustainability, social responsibility, capacity building, course facilitation, project management, inter- and multidisciplinarity, innovations, socio-tec.hnical interaction, developing countries, System of Rice Intensification (SRI)",
